<h2>Overview</h2>
<p>The Sig P365 has gained immense popularity among concealed carry enthusiasts for its compact size and capacity. However, with updates to its design, particularly the striker sleeve, some users may find themselves needing guidance on how to properly disassemble the slide. This tutorial aims to clarify the new process for disassembling the P365 slide, especially for those who may be familiar with earlier versions or similar models.</p>

<h2>What This Video Demonstrates</h2>
<p>In this video, the host walks through the procedure for removing the back plate from the Sig P365 slide, emphasizing the differences in the new striker sleeve design. This updated model changes how the striker assembly is accessed, requiring adjustments from previous methods. The demonstration provides step-by-step instructions while highlighting key changes that users should be aware of.</p>

<h2>Step-by-Step Explanation</h2>
<p>The process begins with ensuring the firearm is unloaded and safe to handle. Once this is confirmed, the following steps are outlined:</p>
<ol>
    <li><strong>Compress the Striker Assembly:</strong> Unlike older models where a simple press would suffice, users must push the striker sleeve towards the front sight. This movement may feel slightly different due to the new design.</li>
    <li><strong>Engage the Catch:</strong> For the updated P365, you need to push the catch on the striker sleeve to the left. This action frees the sleeve for the next step.</li>
    <li><strong>Remove the Back Plate:</strong> With the striker sleeve disengaged, the back plate can now be removed. Care should be taken to avoid any potential spring rebound.</li>
    <li><strong>Reassembly:</strong> When it comes time to reassemble, ensuring that the firing pin block safety is pushed in can facilitate smoother reinstallation of the back plate.</li>
</ol>

<h2>Key Tips</h2>
<p>It’s essential to notice that the tooling and agility required for disassembly and assembly might be different due to the new striker sleeve. Here are some additional tips:</p>
<ul>
    <li>If you’re new to the P365 or have previously owned older models, take your time to understand this new mechanism. It’s crucial for safety and proper function.</li>
    <li>Utilizing proper lighting can help ensure that you can see the changes clearly, especially when handling small parts.</li>
    <li>If unsure about any step, consider referring to additional resources or discussions from the community for further clarity.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Key Takeaways</h2>
<p>With the updates to the Sig P365's striker sleeve, it's essential for users to familiarize themselves with the disassembly process thoroughly. This tutorial not only highlights the step-by-step method but also encourages engagement with other users to share experiences and insights on the changes made. Keeping abreast of these modifications ensures that your maintenance and understanding of the firearm remain top-notch, ultimately enhancing both safety and performance.</p>

